Group the bike rentals by hour, weekday, & client type

Trips %>%
  group_by(lubridate::hour(sdate), lubridate::wday(sdate), client)%>%
  summarise(count = n())%>%
  rename(hour = "lubridate::hour(sdate)")%>%
  rename(wday = "lubridate::wday(sdate)")%>%
  ggplot(aes(x = hour, y = count,colour = client)) +
  geom_smooth(method="loess")+
  facet_wrap(~ wday)+
  theme_bw()
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'lubridate::hour(sdate)', 'lubridate::wday(sdate)'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.

Construct a similar plot using density rather than frequency

Trips %>%
  ggplot()+
  aes(x = lubridate::hour(sdate), color = client) +
  geom_density()+
  facet_wrap(vars(lubridate::wday(sdate)))+
  labs(x = "days in a month") +
  theme_bw()

Section: How Far?

We want to calculate the distance between stations using the haversine() function. The source() function actually runs an R script found at some URL. Use a web browser to visit this URL and read about the function (its only a few lines).

source("https://mdbeckman.github.io/dcSupplement/R/haversine.R") 
Simple <-
  Stations %>%
  select(name, lat, long) %>%
  rename(sstation = name)

Simple2 <-
  Simple %>%
  rename(estation = sstation, lat2 = lat, long2 = long)
StationPairs <- merge(Simple, Simple2, by = NULL)

PairDistances <-
  StationPairs %>%
  mutate(distance = haversine(lat, long, lat2, long2)) %>%
  select(sstation, estation, distance)
  • There will be 120409 cases
  • Cause one station could either be a start one or aa end one
Trips %>%
  inner_join(PairDistances)%>%
  ggplot()+
  aes(x = distance) +
  geom_density(color = "blue")+
  labs(x = "Trip Distance (km)")+
  theme_bw()
Joining, by = c("sstation", "estation")

 PairDistances%>%
  ggplot()+
  aes(x = distance) +
  geom_density(color = "blue")+
  labs(x = "Trip Distance (km)")+
  theme_bw()

They have similar density distribution but different density scale. Because distance is the same.

Section: Mapping the Stations

library(leaflet)
stationMap <-
  leaflet(Stations) %>%           # like ggplot()
  addTiles() %>%                  # add the map
  addCircleMarkers(radius = 2, color = "red") %>%
  setView(-77.04, 38.9, zoom = 12)
Assuming "long" and "lat" are longitude and latitude, respectively
stationMap

Section: Long-distance stations (Extra Credit)

median_distance<-
  PairDistances %>%
  group_by(sstation) %>%
  summarise(mid = 300 * median(distance))
new_stationMap <-
  Stations %>%
  left_join(median_distance, by = c("name" = "sstation"))
new_stationMap <-
  leaflet(new_stationMap) %>%           # like ggplot()
  addTiles() %>%                  # add the map
  addCircles(radius = ~ mid, color = "blue", opacity = 0.0001) %>%
  setView(-77.04, 38.9, zoom = 12)
Assuming "long" and "lat" are longitude and latitude, respectively
new_stationMap
